"v.变得消瘦；衰弱 【英】 v. 衰弱(to lose vigor or vitality)； 【考】 反义词：thrive(茁壮 成长) 【例】 She languished for his love and gave him languishing looks. v. 衰弱; 萎靡不振 = pine 【记】langui拼: 懒鬼－衰弱; 萎靡不振 【反】thrive(v 兴旺; 旺盛) 【记】language 学语言(英语，GRE)学得都憔悴了；可能来自langu- 舌头，语言，因为舌头是无力的；音：懒鬼 languish (v.)  early 14c., ""fail in strength, exhibit signs of approaching death,"" from languiss-, present participle stem of Old French languir ""be listless, pine, grieve, fall ill,"" from Vulgar Latin *languire, from Latin languere ""be weak or faint"" (see lax). Weaker sense ""be lovesick, grieve, lament, grow faint,"" is from mid-14c. Related: Languished; languishing."
